This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with wireless sensor networks and proposes a routing protocol to overcome energy constraints and finite lifetimes. It may also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as it proposes a clustering technique to efficiently manage the network. Additionally, it may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it proposes a unique technique for clustering. It may also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it deals with monitoring environments and managing energy resources. Finally, it may belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it uses a confidence interval to visualize the maximum deviation from the original course.
